message: The Greg's Japanese Auto story started in Alaska on a chilly winter morning in 1984. Greg Huntley, Greg's Japanese Auto founder helped a woman stranded on the side of the road start her car. His good deed was quickly transformed into a business when he and his brother David, got an old mail truck, painted it orange and stocked it with recycled batteries. Greg drove around each day before the morning and evening commute looking for stranded motorists. One day, he couldn't get a car to start, so he towed it home to fix it. Soon, they had a full-time technician and regular customers. The lessons Greg and David learned in Alaska are the foundation of Greg's Japanese Auto right here in Puget Sound. Treat your customers right and not only will they come back, they'll bring their friends and family with them. Today the business includes over 65 employees, service centers in Renton, Bellevue, Federal Way, Covington, Puyallup, Seattle, South Center and Lynnwood.
